Task 1¶

Web scraping and analysis¶

We will use a package called BeautifulSoup to collect the data from the web. Once we've collected our data and saved it into a local .csv file we'll start the analysis.

Scraping data from Skytrax¶

If you visit [https://www.airlinequality.com] you can see that there is a lot of data there. For this task, we are only interested in reviews related to British Airways and the Airline itself.

If you navigate to this link: [https://www.airlinequality.com/airline-reviews/british-airways] you will see this data. Now, we can use Python and BeautifulSoup to collect all the links to the reviews and then to collect the text data on each of the individual review links.

# importing the required libraries

import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import pandas as pd
In [2]:
# writing the code to scrap the data

base_url = "https://www.airlinequality.com/airline-reviews/british-airways"
pages = 50 # specifying the number of pages
page_size = 100 # specifying the page size

reviews = []

# for i in range(1, pages + 1):
for i in range(1, pages + 1):

    print(f"Scraping page {i}")

    # Create URL to collect links from paginated data
    url = f"{base_url}/page/{i}/?sortby=post_date%3ADesc&pagesize={page_size}"

    # Collect HTML data from this page
    response = requests.get(url)

    # Parse content
    content = response.content
    parsed_content = BeautifulSoup(content, 'html.parser')
    for para in parsed_content.find_all("div", {"class": "text_content"}):
        reviews.append(para.get_text())
    
    print(f"   ---> {len(reviews)} total reviews")

Now we have our dataset for this task! The loops above collected 5000 reviews by iterating through the paginated pages on the website.

The next thing that we will do is clean this data to remove any unnecessary text from each of the rows. For example, " Trip Verified" can be removed from each row if it exists, as it's not relevant to what we want to investigate.

# Load the data into a pandas DataFrame
data = pd.read_csv("datareview.csv")

# Preprocess the text data

data["clean_text"] = data["reviews"].str.lower()  # Convert text to lowercase

data['clean_text'] = data['clean_text'].str.replace('trip verified', '')

# Remove leading and trailing whitespaces
data['clean_text'] = data['clean_text'].str.strip()

# Remove punctuation and numbers
data["clean_text"] = data["clean_text"].str.replace("[^\w\s]", "")
data["clean_text"] = data["clean_text"].str.replace("\d+", "")

# Remove stopwords
stop_words = set(stopwords.words("english"))
data["clean_text"] = data["clean_text"].apply(
    lambda x: " ".join(word for word in nltk.word_tokenize(x) if word not in stop_words)
)

# Perform lemmatization
lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()
data["clean_text"] = data["clean_text"].apply(
    lambda x: " ".join(lemmatizer.lemmatize(word) for word in nltk.word_tokenize(x))
)

# Remove remaining special characters
data["clean_text"] = data["clean_text"].str.replace("[^\w\s]", "")

# Remove duplicates
data = data.drop_duplicates(subset=["clean_text"])

#  carrying out Sentiment Analysis using the SentimentIntensityAnalyzer

sid = SentimentIntensityAnalyzer()
data["sentiment"] = data["clean_text"].apply(lambda x: sid.polarity_scores(x)["compound"])

# Descriptive Analysis
review_lengths = data["clean_text"].apply(lambda x: len(x.split()))
plt.hist(review_lengths, bins=20)
plt.xlabel("Review Length")
plt.ylabel("Frequency")
plt.show()

# Word Cloud
all_reviews = " ".join(data["clean_text"])
wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=400).generate(all_reviews)
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation="bilinear")
plt.axis("off")

In [12]:
# Topic Modeling using LDA
vectorizer = CountVectorizer(max_features=1000, lowercase=True, stop_words="english")
tf_matrix = vectorizer.fit_transform(data["clean_text"])
lda_model = LatentDirichletAllocation(n_components=20, random_state=42)
lda_model.fit(tf_matrix)

 # Extracting topics
topic_keywords = pd.DataFrame(lda_model.components_, columns=vectorizer.get_feature_names())
top_topics = topic_keywords.idxmax(axis=1)
data["topic"] = top_topics


# Identify common positive and negative words
positive_words = " ".join(data[data["sentiment"] > 0]["clean_text"])
negative_words = " ".join(data[data["sentiment"] < 0]["clean_text"])

# Identify topics and their distribution
topic_distribution = data["topic"].value_counts()

# Provide recommendations based on analysis

positive_words_df = pd.DataFrame({"word": positive_words.split()})

# Count the occurrences of positive and negative words
positive_word_counts = positive_words_df["word"].value_counts()
negative_word_counts = negative_words_df["word"].value_counts()

positive_themes = positive_word_counts.index.tolist()
negative_themes = negative_word_counts.index.tolist()

axes[0].set_title('Most Common Positive Words')
